about emma makoba emma makoba stanford center on longevity skip to content home about about my name is emma makoba and welcome to my blog i m from reno nevada and am currently a freshman at stanford university i have yet to decide on a major but am very interested in the field of public health my father's side of the family still lives in a rural village in uganda growing up i was always aware of not only the poverty that my father was able to escape through education but also the poverty some of my relatives continue to endure my grandmother because of limited access to health care in the region died prematurely and without cause of a severe case of pneumonia that was left neglected and untreated we don t see this kind of death in the developed world the fact that my grandmother died of an infection high lights one of the most pressing issues facing health policy makers in the third world how will we address the increasing burden of chronic disease in the aging populace while not abandoning the infectious diseases that still ravage the population in my blog i hope to disscuss this impending public health crisis from multiple angles taking into account everything from the types of disease to funding policy making and ethics leave a reply cancel reply your email address will not be published required fields are marked name email website comment you may use these html tags and attributes a href title abbr title acronym title b blockquote cite cite code del datetime em i q cite strike strong search for recent posts so what do we do now solutions to chronic disease part ii so what do we do now solutions to chronic disease part i three major players in the battle to fight disease in the words of my father a ugandan's perspective alphabet soup the daly the yll and the qualy what does it all mean recent comments archives june 2011 may 2011 april 2011 categories uncategorized meta log in entries rss comments rss wordpress org emma makoba proudly powered by wordpress
